---
description: Motion and animation conventions for the ID-Components motion system
globs:
  - packages/motion/**/*.ts
  - packages/core/**/*.tsx
---

All animation goes through `@id-components/motion`. Direct `gsap` imports are forbidden in
`packages/core`.

Pattern:
```ts
const { presets, intent, reducedMotion } = useMotion();
const ref = useRef<HTMLElement>(null);
useTimeline(ref, (tl) => {
  if (reducedMotion) return;
  const p = presets[intent].hover;
  tl.to(ref.current, { scale: p.scale, duration: p.duration, ease: p.ease });
});
```

- Default intent is `'playful'`. `intent="professional"` is the explicit opt-out.
- Always guard GSAP calls with `if (reducedMotion) return;`.
- Motion presets in `packages/motion/src/index.ts` define durations and easings only.
- Components own the actual `gsap.to()` / `tl.to()` calls — presets just supply the numbers.
